text: Eupterote kageri is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Nässig in 1989. It is found on Sumatra. Adults range from bright whitish yellow to deep yellow with black markings and usually two, mostly quite prominent dark dots in the anal angle of the forewings.A new species of Eupterote from Sumatra ==References== Category:Moths described in 1989 Category:Eupterotinae
title: Eupterote kageri
